Movie: Doctor Who: The Church on Ruby Road
Review: a rough 4, for surencuti has me sold, kinda amazing that he’s the first non-adorkable doctor in, like, 20 years? dude’s just hot and charming as hell, knows it, rolls with it, and sells practically every line without breaking a sweat. millie gibson though? shes alright. honestly, apart from gatwa, im not super sold on the supporting cast, which is worryingwill say, this is the gayest doctor who has maybe ever been but only 65% of that feels…
damn solid, hoping for more but am pretty content with what this is, all things considered

an odyssey of sorts, thick with its own nefarious and ethereal magic, Manhunter is much like a fresh cut wound by steel wire in dark winter, insofar as it stings like a motherfucker and burns in the freeze. Petersen and Cox also give all-timer performances (the latter providing Lecter with an arrogance I quickly got addicted to), so all in all i’m calling this a massive W for me considering its my first film of 2024. here’s to the rest of the year!
